<title type="html"><![CDATA[NES Controller reading done wrong with no input?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7411&amp;p=73087#p73087"><![CDATA[
I don't know what exactly you need to detect this for, but "for safety" you could add some extra checks, so that if 9th bit is 0, but any of the 1st-8th bit are non-zero (user is pressing buttons), set a flag to ignore the controller detection.<br /><br />So let's say you want to pause the game when no controller is detected. This way it would only pause it at the beginning of the game/whatever, and after user pressed START, it would work fine after that (with controller detection disabled).<br /><br />This could be detected seamlessly in a menu. However it wouldn't work perfectly if user decided to switch to a different controller after the fact. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /> But it wouldn't break the game either. And of course it would be possible to check it while the game is running too... I just don't feel like it's a very important feature since I don't ever remember the controllers coming loose by accident.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=80">thefox</a> — Mon Jan 24, 2011 4:26 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
