<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7411&amp;p=73012#p73012"><![CDATA[
You can't detect when a controller is plugged or removed. The NES has internal pull-up resistor, so when no controller is inserted, it reads all 1's like when a controller is inserted but no button is pressed<br /><br />I don't know how you can detect it... Does the NES has direct access to the latch clock line?<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4431">socram8888</a> — Sat Jan 22, 2011 10:31 am</p><hr />
